Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.80,0:05:33.05,辉注,,0,0,0,,百事可乐天下第一！不服来辩！
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.08,0:00:03.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期Primal Space由ExpressVPN赞助
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.08,0:00:03.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,This episode of Primal Space is supported by ExpressVPN
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.36,0:00:10.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,1996年4月2日 国际巨星辛迪·克劳馥 克劳迪娅·希弗 安德烈·阿加西
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.36,0:00:10.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the 2nd of April 1996, global superstars Cindy Crawford, Claudia Schiffer and Andre Agassi
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.88,0:00:14.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,站在伦敦盖特威克机场的跑道上 等待着一架飞机的到来
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.88,0:00:14.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,stood on the runway at Gatwick Airport, waiting for a plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.22,0:00:21.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,但他们不是要飞往国外某地 因为事件的焦点是那架飞机本身
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.22,0:00:21.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,But they weren't there to fly to some exotic destination, the event was the plane itself;
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.21,0:00:26.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,一架全新金属蓝涂装 印有显眼的百事可乐logo的协和客机
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.21,0:00:26.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,a freshly painted, electric blue concorde, emblazoned with the Pepsi logo.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:26.93,0:00:30.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,今天我们将回顾90年代最大规模的市场营销事件之一
Dialogue: 2,0:00:26.93,0:00:30.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Today we're going to look at one of the biggest marketing stunts of the 90s
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.88,0:00:37.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,并了解如此普通的涂装是怎样给这款超音速客机带来严重技术问题的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.88,0:00:37.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,and see how something as simple as a paint job created a serious technical issue for this supersonic airliner.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.52,0:00:42.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,在90年代中叶 百事可乐决定更换他们的设计
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.52,0:00:42.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,During the mid 90's, Pepsi had decided it was time to change their design.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.69,0:00:47.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们易拉罐上红色元素太多 和其头号对手可口可乐有点撞衫
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.69,0:00:47.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,There was too much red on their cans which clashed with their rivals, Coca Cola.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.07,0:00:49.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以他们重新设计出近乎全蓝的包装
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.07,0:00:49.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, they rebranded to a mostly blue can
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.62,0:00:53.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,为此他们需要在全世界进行一次大规模宣传活动
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.62,0:00:53.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and needed a big campaign to announce this change to the world.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.28,0:00:55.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,史称“蓝色计划”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.28,0:00:55.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so began 'Project Blue'.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.04,0:00:57.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们和法国航空商量好
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.04,0:00:57.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,They struck a deal with Air France,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.96,0:01:02.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,允许他们为当时20架协和客机中的一架重新涂装
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.96,0:01:02.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,allowing them to repaint one of the 20 concordes in existence at the time.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.40,0:01:07.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,实际上他们拿到了当时最新生产的协和客机 注册号F-BTSD
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.40,0:01:07.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, they got one of the last concordes to be made, Sierra Delta.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.29,0:01:13.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,该飞机于1978年制造 得益于新的工艺技术
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.29,0:01:13.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,This particular Concorde was built in 1978 and benefitted from new construction techniques
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.39,0:01:17.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如钛合金铆钉 让它成为了最轻的协和客机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.39,0:01:17.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,like the use of titanium rivets, which made it much lighter than other Concordes.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,直到今天 F-BTSD也仍拥有最快环球旅行的时间记录
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,To this day, Sierra Delta holds the record for the fastest circumnavigation of the globe,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.10,0:01:29.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,耗时31小时27分钟49秒 经停六次加油
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.10,0:01:29.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,taking 31 hours 27 minutes and 49 seconds including 6 stops for fuel.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.60,0:01:35.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,拿到了最合适的协和客机后 百事可乐为发布会又定好了良辰吉日 开始干活了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.60,0:01:35.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,With the most capable Concorde at their disposal, Pepsi set a date for their big event and got to work.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.69,0:01:40.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,全新涂装是在法国航空位于巴黎的机库内秘密喷涂的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.69,0:01:40.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,The new paint job was carried out in secrecy at an Air France facility in Paris,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:40.41,0:01:45.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,花费超过200升颜料 上千人几小时的工作才完成
Dialogue: 2,0:01:40.41,0:01:45.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,requiring over 200 litres of paint and thousands of man hours to complete.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.45,0:01:49.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,当最后一滴颜料晾干 他们马上把飞机用棕色纸包起来
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.45,0:01:49.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once the last drop was dry, they quickly wrapped the aircraft in brown paper
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.58,0:01:51.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,以保证营销内容保密
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.58,0:01:51.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,to make sure the stunt was kept secret.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:52.01,0:01:55.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,而发布会在伦敦 他们又在晚上跨越了英吉利海峡来到英国
Dialogue: 2,0:01:52.01,0:01:55.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the big event was in London, they sped across the English Channel during the night,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:55.75,0:02:00.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,在停进伦敦盖特威克机场一个机库之前一直保密得很好
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.75,0:02:00.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,remaining undercover before being escorted straight to a hanger at Gatwick airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.52,0:02:03.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,全球各地的记者都受邀来到机库
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.52,0:02:03.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Journalists from all over the world had been invited to the hangar,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.58,0:02:08.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,参加由克劳馥 希弗 阿加西三人主打的新广告
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.58,0:02:08.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,being told that they would see a new ad, featuring Crawford, Schiffer and Agassi.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.50,0:02:11.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后就是90年代能想到的最牛逼的画面了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.50,0:02:11.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,What followed was the most 90's event imaginable,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,绚烂的灯光秀配上骑摩托入场的超模
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,a futuristic light show with supermodels arriving on motorbikes.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.10,0:02:20.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,一番渲染之后 蓝色的协和客机被拉进昏暗的机库
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.10,0:02:20.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,After the main ad was introduced, the blue concorde was wheeled into the dark hangar,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.86,0:02:23.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,在隐约的迷雾和闪光灯中揭开了真面目
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.86,0:02:23.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,through a fog of smoke machines and strobe lights.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.08,0:02:27.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,这场发布会花了百事可乐大约五百万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.08,0:02:27.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,This event cost Pepsi around 5 million dollars to produce,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.78,0:02:31.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,成为了当时最昂贵的广告
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.78,0:02:31.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,making it the most expensive ad ever made at the time.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.29,0:02:35.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这不是“蓝色计划”中唯一一个公众营销事件
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.29,0:02:35.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this wasn't the only publicity stunt in the Project Blue campaign.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.69,0:02:37.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,在协和客机公布之前几个月
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.69,0:02:37.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just a month after the Concorde unveiling,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.98,0:02:42.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,百事可乐成为了第一个在太空打商业广告的公司
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.98,0:02:42.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Pepsi became the first ever company to shoot a commercial in space.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.20,0:02:48.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,和平号空间站上的俄罗斯宇航员在太空行走时展示了百事新包装的模型
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.20,0:02:48.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Cosmonauts onboard the Mir space station took a large replica of the new Pepsi can on a space walk.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.25,0:02:51.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个广告又花了百事可乐五百万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.25,0:02:51.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,This ad cost Pepsi another 5 million dollars to produce.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.00,0:02:57.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,但广告结束后 百事就换设计了 广告中的设计也就石沉大海了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.00,0:02:57.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,But once the ad was finished, Pepsi had changed the design of the can and the ad was never aired.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.98,0:03:02.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们在之前某期Primal Space中详细介绍过此事与其他充满野心的太空广告
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.98,0:03:02.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,We go into this and other ambitious space adverts in a previous Primal Space video.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.37,0:03:07.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,协和客机的新涂装公布后 百事可乐就带它进行了一次巡演
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.37,0:03:07.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,After Concorde's new look was unveiled, Pepsi took the plane on a promotional tour,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.62,0:03:10.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,飞往了欧洲和中东的十个城市
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.62,0:03:10.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,jetting off to 10 different cities across Europe and the Middle East.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.09,0:03:13.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 这期间遇到了问题
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.09,0:03:13.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, there was one major condition.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.22,0:03:15.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们需要飞慢点
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.22,0:03:15.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,They had to reduce the speed.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.49,0:03:19.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,协和客机的典型巡航速度是2.04马赫
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.49,0:03:19.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,The typical cruising speed for a concorde was Mach 2.04.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:19.69,0:03:22.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,但以此速度飞行会产生大量的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:03:19.69,0:03:22.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,But flying at this speed generated a huge amount of heat.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.04,0:03:27.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,部分原因是流经机身表面的空气与之摩擦
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.04,0:03:27.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was partly due to the friction of the air passing over the surface of the aircraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.26,0:03:31.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,不是所有气流可以快速离开超音速客机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.26,0:03:31.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,with supersonic aircraft, not all the air can move out of the way fast enough.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.44,0:03:35.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,这会让空气被压缩 并在机头产生高温区域
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.44,0:03:35.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,This compresses the air and creates an area of high pressure in front of the nose,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.53,0:03:36.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,让飞机变热
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.53,0:03:36.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,which heats up the plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.21,0:03:40.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,全速飞行时 机头温度可以达到127摄氏度
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.21,0:03:40.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,At full speed, the nose would get as hot as 127 degrees
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.81,0:03:43.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃料箱和机翼可以超过90摄氏度
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.81,0:03:43.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the fuselage and the wings exceeding 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.88,0:03:48.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,这会让飞机以肉眼可见的程度膨胀30毫米
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.88,0:03:48.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,This would cause the aircraft to visibly expand by around 30 mm.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.34,0:03:51.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,在驾驶舱内 你会发现飞行机师面板和后舱壁的缝隙会变大
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.34,0:03:51.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Inside the cockpit, you could see this happening and a gap would open up
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.98,0:03:54.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,在驾驶舱内 你会发现飞行机师面板和后舱壁的缝隙会变大
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.98,0:03:54.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,between the flight engineer's console and the bulkhead.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.85,0:03:58.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,在一些退役的飞机中 你还会看到里面夹着一个帽子
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.85,0:03:58.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,On some of the retired planes, you can actually see a cap that was placed in the gap
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.97,0:04:02.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,就是在该飞机最后一次飞行时放进去的 冷却后就卡在里面了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.97,0:04:02.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,on the final flight, becoming trapped, once the metal shrank again.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.94,0:04:06.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,这种膨胀在所有超音速飞机中都是个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.94,0:04:06.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,This expansion is a problem in all supersonic planes.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.62,0:04:10.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,最快的飞机 洛克希德的黑鸟SR-71
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.62,0:04:10.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fastest jet ever created, the Lockheed SR-71 blackbird,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.61,0:04:13.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,就是由各自可以膨胀的很多小零件制造的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.61,0:04:13.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,was built with many small parts that could each expand.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.18,0:04:18.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,这会导致飞机在跑道上的时候会漏油
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.18,0:04:18.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,This would often cause the aircraft to have fuel leaks whilst sitting on the runway.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,协和客机的设计就是要尽可能降低表面的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Concorde was designed to limit surface heat as much as possible.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.28,0:04:26.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以使用了特殊的白色颜料 不但有法国特色 还可以比一般的飞机反射更多热量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.28,0:04:26.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,They used a special white paint that was much more reflective than typical aircraft paint,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.73,0:04:28.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以使用了特殊的白色颜料 不但有法国特色 还可以比一般的飞机反射更多热量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.73,0:04:28.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,allowing it to radiate more heat.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.92,0:04:32.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,飞机的燃料也在表面散热中起到关键作用
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.92,0:04:32.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,The jet fuel played a key role in absorbing a lot of the surface heat,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:32.10,0:04:34.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,从而让飞机保持在正常温度
Dialogue: 2,0:04:32.10,0:04:34.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,helping to keep the aircraft at a nominal temperature.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.05,0:04:40.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使有了这些保护 正常飞行时客舱的墙壁摸起来也是暖暖的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:35.05,0:04:40.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even with all this protection, surfaces inside the cabin became warm to the touch during a normal flight.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.95,0:04:43.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以 对于新的蓝色涂装
